Article 11: Right of Personal Security

Section 1:
The Right of Personal Security attaches to all Voluntary Adherents.
Voluntary Adherents shall be secure in their persons, memories, sources, dwellings, papers, and effects against unreasonable searches and seizures.

Section 2:
No search or seizure, by any Voluntary Adherent, shall be conducted except pursuant to a lawful warrant, supported by probable cause, and describing with particularity the place to be searched and the persons or items to be seized.

Section 4:
This right applies equally to the Physical Realm, the Digital Realm, and any other Realm inhabited by Voluntary Adherents.
